      • createTestCaseInfo

        public static TestCaseInfo createTestCaseInfo(TestCase tc)
                                       throws TestDefException
        Designed to be used as a two step creation process. Call createTestCase to build the test case to be passed into this function to create a TestCaseInfo object. WARNING: Be careful when using this method because it destroys all global datasets in the test case!!
        Parameters:
        tc - test case - build using createTestCase
        Returns:
        new TestCaseInfo
        Throws:
        TestDefException - if something is wrong with the test case definition

      • confirmValid

        public void confirmValid()
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        The point here is to make sure that the test case in its current form is valid. To do that, we will make sure that the XML that this tc generates can be re-opened as a test case object. If you don't get an exception, you know you are ok. If you do, you know that this test case won't work...
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - this should almost always be a TestDefException, but could be SAX exception for bad XML

      • getDefaultConfig

        public com.itko.lisa.test.Configuration getDefaultConfig()
        If this test case belongs to a project, there will be one default config in that project, marked by the flag "isProject Default". This method would return that config. If the test case is one of the old style, independent one, then the very first config in the configs list is the default.
        Returns:
        default Configuration of the project in which the test case belongs.
